    "Thereby, ample opportunities allow experiences of autonomy, competence, and relatedness fuelling intrinsic motivation.",
    "\"In a well-designed game, the learning becomes its own reward\" (Ryan & Rigby, 2020, p. 169).",
    "The problem-based gaming model (Kiili, 2007) further emphasizes the meaning of experiential learning and reflection in educational games.",
    "It is argued that the ability to reflect may be the main factor determining who learns effectively from experience (Kiili, 2007).",
    "This is especially true for games that require problem-solving (e.g., simulation games)."
